@taos・79 Hello all, we do not expect much new things released this week, as we are deeply involved in developing two big "next things," or rather currently testing them out and developing the last bits them:

1. short-selling and margin-buying features are going to be enabled for the AI Agents as soon as possible (unlikely this week, though) – this means that one could develop strategies that take bigger positions even in the case the asset owned are not enough currently, being able to leverage rather;

2. "AI template(s)" to go with this kind of development of "riskier position building" and covering quickly for those positions using AI approaches – recall that since our initial launch, we have stated that ML/DL approaches could and should be considered in combination with "speed" and this remains our main goal.

The AI template(s) are intended to become the mainstay of the approaches taken, since the markets are inherently dynamic and the real applications to real data will warrant such. But we do not want to throw just plan "AI algorithms" at you, though, as you can easily find them online yourself. We want to build a road that could be taken to its logical end, which is "deep HFT," which is intelligence + speed.

More technical details of the progressions will be released this week as per @6/. , as then our internal tests are expected to be completed. Releasing the short-selling etc features prematurely could do some unwanted damage. In the right knowing hands, such positions can do a lot of good to the market, as most academic evidenec suggests these advanced features do stabilize rather than instabiliize.

Also, we should note that this week we can provide further graphical evidence of the status of the network, how different keys are performing with the said tools above, and help newcomers to become more prominent in mining. These tools would help to adapt the right AI tools as well. We expect more collaborations to happen and will leverage even to academic institutions we are connected to.

@taos・79 Hello all, to confirm, we are still working on the short-selling and margin-buying features, to confirm they work well. These are done to the level of detail of most exchanges in crypto, but we start with a bit "limited" feature stack in that our system will not allow "two directions" taken at the same time, you cannot go margin-buying while in short-selling position, or vice versa – your order is blocked. Later, we may consider relaxing this a bit to be consistent with some exchanges.

There are couple of more more nuanced things in check, and @6/. can maybe make further comments on those.

Then, we are also working on the new dashboard, so we expect there to be 2-3 major things coming out next week, or the week after at the latest. These are done to set the stage for newcomers to the network, and improve advanced guys' chances to be more profitable. Essentially to give different variations to exist. Plus we want to incentivize true AI algorithm building. We will keep you guys posted here. We will also post some figures of the tools you could also use to analyze this Sn, and others.

@taos・79 Our technology side will update here momentarily, they are busy doing some last minute checks, lots of stuff being tested. After this week, we are going back to the Limit-Order-Book modelling and resolving certain issues of the timing of order arrivals, plus working on modelling of bubbles and crashes to increase the applicability to real world.

The release today at the typical Wednesday 5pm UTC include:

- AI Template, which will likely be also updated later this week for further accuracy – this AI Template is the first serious step towards more complicated AI models, which we recommend looking at, since this is not speed-first reaction, but intelligence-first application; more AI support will also be coming, but we expect the AI Agents themselves to develop further ideas primarily, while we are going to release certain typical frameworks that may be useful in the operations;

- Updates to fix the bug in certain (quite rate) cases related to the accounting of short-selling and margin-buying, this has been identified, but the full solution to handle it may still require time to fix unfortunately, meanwhile making the best effort not to allow the system to crash in just cases; to be clearer, this bug is about very small decimals accuracy errors in accounting of AI Agents actions, which in C++ accumulate to the extent that they are hard to diagnose and take care of;

- Validator switch would be announced as per the earlier pre-announcement on Monday, and we are also prepared to standby to make sure it will be sufficient – more details technically will be released before 5pm UTC today.

