@taos・79 Hello guys, we are starting a "new series" of "trade cards" which show-case now some examples of actual trading strategy performances. This idea will be elaborated on, and the "cards" will be also made a bit more visually attractive over time. The idea being to help to study the best and the worst of the bunch being active on the net.

I can say that some of those using basic strategies that are "dumb," or do not adjust to increased volatility, momentum, and so on, will likely be on the loser side. This is because we are approaching more realistic versions of the real markets, inch by inch, and this means that the considerations of when to trade and when not to trade become more crucial.

Anyhow, here's some first tasters, for which we can also provide some more insight on! We hope you find these interesting.
